## 2. FONT LOADING — next/font Setup

In `app/layout.tsx` — load all three faces here. Never import fonts in component files.

```tsx
// app/layout.tsx
import { Instrument_Serif } from 'next/font/google'
import { IBM_Plex_Mono } from 'next/font/google'
import { GeistSans } from 'geist/font/sans'  // npm: geist

const instrumentSerif = Instrument_Serif({
  weight: '400',
  subsets: ['latin'],
  display: 'swap',
  variable: '--font-serif',
})

const ibmPlexMono = IBM_Plex_Mono({
  weight: ['400', '500'],
  subsets: ['latin'],
  display: 'swap',
  variable: '--font-mono',
})

// GeistSans is a variable font — use its built-in variable export
// GeistSans.variable gives you --font-geist-sans

export default function RootLayout({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {
  return (
    <html
      lang="en"
      className={`${instrumentSerif.variable} ${ibmPlexMono.variable} ${GeistSans.variable}`}
    >
      <body className="font-sans bg-surface text-olive-900 antialiased">
        {children}
      </body>
    </html>
  )
}
```

### Font Assignment Rules — Which Tag Maps to Which Face

| Element | Font | Tailwind Class | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| Page title (h1) | Instrument Serif | `font-serif text-display` | Student profile name, dashboard title |
| Section title (h2) | Instrument Serif | `font-serif text-title` | Card headers, report section titles |
| Subsection (h3) | Geist 600 | `font-sans text-subhead font-semibold` | Table column groups, panel titles |
| Body text | Geist 400 | `font-sans text-body` | Descriptions, session summaries, labels |
| Small labels | Geist 500 | `font-sans text-label font-medium uppercase tracking-wide` | Field labels, table headers |
| Nav items | Geist 500 | `font-sans text-body font-medium` | Sidebar navigation |
| All numbers | IBM Plex Mono | `font-mono text-data` | EVERY count, percentage, date in a table |
| KPI values | IBM Plex Mono | `font-mono text-data-lg font-medium` | Incident count headline, % reduction |
| Incident counts in tables | IBM Plex Mono | `font-mono text-data tabular-nums` | Ensures column alignment |
| Goal completion % | IBM Plex Mono | `font-mono text-data` | Always mono, never sans |
| Dates in tables | IBM Plex Mono | `font-mono text-data-sm text-olive-600` | |
| Button labels | Geist 500 | `font-sans text-body font-medium` | |
| Badge text | Geist 500 | `font-sans text-label font-medium` | Status badges |
| Error messages | Geist 400 | `font-sans text-body-sm text-error` | Inline validation |
| Caption / helper text | Geist 400 | `font-sans text-caption text-olive-500` | Below inputs, footnotes |

**Rule:** `font-mono` is used EXCLUSIVELY for data values. Never for labels, headings, descriptions, or UI text. If it is a number in a data context, it is mono. No exceptions.

