## 4. DATA DISPLAY CONVENTIONS

### 4.1 Numeric Formatting Rules

**IBM Plex Mono is used for ANY number in a data context. Zero exceptions.**

| Data Type | Format | Tailwind Classes |
|---|---|---|
| Incident count (headline KPI) | `12` | `font-mono text-data-lg font-medium text-olive-900` |
| Percent reduction (positive = bad) | `+23%` or `-62%` | `font-mono text-data-lg font-medium` + color below |
| Percent reduction in tables | `-62.5%` | `font-mono text-data tabular-nums` |
| Goal completion rate | `87%` | `font-mono text-data text-olive-800` |
| Suspension days | `3.5 days` | `font-mono text-data` |
| Dates in tables | `Apr 09, 2026` | `font-mono text-data-sm text-olive-600` |
| Duration | `45 min` | `font-mono text-data-sm text-olive-500` |

### 4.2 Trend Indicator Colors

```tsx
// Trend direction — incidents going DOWN is improvement (green)
// Trend direction — incidents going UP is regression (red/amber)

function TrendValue({ deltaPct }: { deltaPct: number }) {
  // deltaPct is signed: negative = fewer incidents = improvement
  const isImprovement = deltaPct < 0
  const isRegression = deltaPct >= 25  // 25%+ spike triggers regression alert color
  const isFlat = deltaPct === 0

  const colorClass = isImprovement
    ? 'text-success'
    : isRegression
    ? 'text-status-regression'
    : isFlat
    ? 'text-olive-500'
    : 'text-warning'

  return (
    <span className={`font-mono text-data font-medium tabular-nums ${colorClass}`}>
      {deltaPct > 0 ? '+' : ''}{deltaPct.toFixed(1)}%
    </span>
  )
}
```

