## 6. ESCALATION ALERT — BLOCKING BANNER

This is a safety-critical component. When `escalation_flag === true` on an AI analysis, this banner renders at the top of the student profile page above all other content. It cannot be dismissed without counselor acknowledgment. Do not downplay it visually.

```tsx
// components/alerts/EscalationBanner.tsx
// Renders at the TOP of StudentProfile page when ai_analysis.escalation_flag === true
// Sits ABOVE the student name header, full width, no margin clipping

interface EscalationBannerProps {
  reason: string
  analysisId: string
  hasBeenAcknowledged: boolean
  onAcknowledge: (analysisId: string, action: string) => Promise<void>
}

export function EscalationBanner({
  reason,
  analysisId,
  hasBeenAcknowledged,
  onAcknowledge,
}: EscalationBannerProps) {
  return (
    <div
      role="alert"
      aria-live="assertive"
      className={`
        w-full px-5 py-4
        border-b-2
        ${hasBeenAcknowledged
          ? 'bg-red-50 border-red-200'
          : 'bg-red-800 border-red-900'
        }
      `}
    >
      <div className="max-w-5xl mx-auto flex items-start gap-4">
        {/* Icon */}
        <div className={`shrink-0 mt-0.5 ${hasBeenAcknowledged ? 'text-red-600' : 'text-white'}`}>
          {/* Lucide AlertTriangle, size 20 */}
          <AlertTriangle size={20} aria-hidden="true" />
        </div>

        {/* Content */}
        <div className="flex-1">
          <p className={`
            font-sans text-subhead font-semibold mb-1
            ${hasBeenAcknowledged ? 'text-red-900' : 'text-white'}
          `}>
            {hasBeenAcknowledged
              ? 'Escalation Acknowledged'
              : 'Escalation Required — Refer to Licensed Clinician'
            }
          </p>
          <p className={`
            font-sans text-body
            ${hasBeenAcknowledged ? 'text-red-800' : 'text-red-100'}
          `}>
            {reason}
          </p>
        </div>

        {/* Acknowledgment action — required before banner changes state */}
        {!hasBeenAcknowledged && (
          <button
            onClick={() => onAcknowledge(analysisId, 'reviewed')}
            className="
              shrink-0 px-4 py-2 rounded
              bg-white text-red-900
              font-sans text-body font-semibold
              hover:bg-red-50
              focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-white focus-visible:ring-offset-2 focus-visible:ring-offset-red-800
              active:bg-red-100
              transition-colors duration-100
              min-h-[40px]
            "
          >
            Acknowledge & Document Action
          </button>
        )}
      </div>
    </div>
  )
}
```

**Escalation banner placement rule:** In the student profile page layout, the EscalationBanner renders as the first child of the page root, before `<StudentProfileHeader>`, before navigation, before any other content. It is not inside a card or panel. It spans the full content width.

**Escalation chip (in dashboard list):** When a student has an unacknowledged escalation flag in the dashboard:

```tsx
// Small chip shown on StudentCard in the dashboard list
<span className="
  inline-flex items-center gap-1
  bg-red-800 text-white
  font-sans text-label font-medium
  px-2 py-0.5 rounded-sm
" aria-label="Escalation flag — requires immediate action">
  <AlertTriangle size={10} aria-hidden="true" />
  Escalation
</span>
```

