## 9. WHAT CURSOR MUST NEVER DO

- Never use `text-gray-300` or `text-gray-400` on a white background — fails WCAG AA
- Never use `text-green-600` or `text-red-600` as the ONLY differentiator between states — always pair with icon or label
- Never hardcode hex values in component files — always use Tailwind semantic tokens from this config
- Never use Inter, Roboto, or Arial in any component
- Never compute chart data, percentages, or aggregations client-side — receive from server props only
- Never use `shadcn/ui` default styles without overriding all color tokens to the olive/gold system
- Never use `purple`, `violet`, `indigo`, or `blue` as primary or accent colors — this system uses only olive and gold
- Never use a pie chart for more than 4 categories
- Never use placeholder text as a label substitute — labels are always above the input field
- Never style a select element with custom CSS that overrides the native browser control on iOS Safari
- Never place the primary action button only in a top navigation bar on mobile
- Never use `font-serif` (Instrument Serif) for body text, form labels, navigation, or numeric data
- Never use `font-sans` (Geist) for incident counts, percentages, dates in tables, or any data value
- Never use a modal when an inline panel or page navigation suffices
- Never produce the escalation banner as anything less than full-width and visually dominant — this is a safety feature
